6 Subject: Health; hospitals; hospital budgets; Green Mountain Care Board;
7 executive compensation; administrative staffing ratios
8 Statement of purpose of bill as introduced: This bill proposes to require
9 hospitals to provide information about employee compensation and
10 administrative staffing ratios to the Green Mountain Care Board as part of the
11 Board’s hospital budget review process. It would also direct the Board to
12 ensure that the ratio of administrative employees at each hospital to employees
13 delivering health care services directly to patients is aligned with national
14 averages for similar hospitals and that the compensation for a hospital’s
15 executive and clinic leadership does not equal more than 10 times that of the
16 hospital’s lowest-paid employees who deliver health care services directly to
17 hospital patients.
